Cell.Text: Any new work to do?
Yes, I have. In my research, I discovered a book about the Totems of Hircine. | Ancient artifacts related to the cult of Hircine and Lycanthropy.
Totems of Hircine?

Yes. There are three: a thigh bone, a carved Skull, and a Drum. | I was searching for clues about where they might be and how to destroy them. | Now I think I discovered where they may be, and how to banish them.
Banish them?

Yes. Since they are daedric artifacts, once they are destroyed there is no guarantee they are gone to come back someday. | I hope our work will last for some generations. | But even in the worst case, it should diminish Hincine influence over Skyrim.
Let's begin!
[S] The first totem is called Totem of the Hunt. Reassemble a thigh bone. It must be hidden in Clearspring Cave. | Take this, a copy of The Totems Of Hircine, if you want to learn more about it.
I'm busy right now...
No problem... Come back when you are ready.
How the first totem looks like?
The first totem is called Totem of the Hunt. Reassemble a thigh bone. It must be hidden in Clearspring Cave.

Cell.Text: I think this is the Totem of the Hunt...
[S] Good job! It matches the totem description. | The second totem must be on Cragwallow Slope. It resembles a usual drum. It is called the Totem of Brotherhood.

Node.Caption: DSilHand_S02_F1T_Topic01: I think this is the Totem of the Hunt...

Cell.Text: Where is the second totem?
The second totem is called Totem of Brotherhood. It resembles a simple drum. It must be inside Cragwallow Slope.
A drum, it must be the Totem of Brotherhood...

[S] Great job again my brother. We are doing well on this quest. It matches the totem description from the book. | The third and last totem is at the Darklight Tower, and held by Hagraven Witches. | It is a carved wolf skull with some feathers attached to it. It is called the Totem of Fear.

Node.Caption: DSilHand_S02_F2T_Topic01: A drum, it must be the Totem of Brotherhood...

Cell.Text: Where is the third totem?
The last totem must be inside the Darklight Tower. It is called Totem of Fear and resembles a Wolf's carved skull.
Here is the Totem of Fear.
[S] Great job! We managed to find all the totems. Now, we must burn them into the flame of the Harbinger inside Ysgramor's tomb.

Node.Caption: DSilHand_S02_F3T_Topic01: Here is the Totem of Fear.

Cell.Text: It is done!

[S] Yes it is. Thanks, brother for your help. I hope this work is going to dim Hircine's influence over Skyrim in the next centuries to come. | Take this sword as a token of my gratitude. Now, I'll go back to Driftshade. If you need me, you will find me there.
